history.content: You will most likely get into both. Pretty sure you are guaranteed to get into CS 61C with that position on the waitlist and being an underclassmen, and most likely will get into CS 170. Both classes are known to accommodate waitlist students as long as you show consistent involvement (doing the first hw/project, going to lecture, going to discussion).

I'm planning to take CS 170 and CS 61C in the Fall, but I am not yet declared as CS. I got waitlisted for both classes and I'm on the 50th position on the waitlist.

What is the chance that I'll get in the class? Am I more likely to get in? or Should I take another class instead?

Thank you!
